description: The truth comes out. Demonstaff was a scientist that had become obsessed by his work. He pushed away his girlfriend and only realized what he had did when it too late. He goes mad, gains cosmic powers and is now threatening all reality in order to win her back. Cosmic and not so cosmic character's clash (Dargo's girlfriend tries her own punches) and in the end Demonstaff finds himself in limbo. To wrap it up, his girl does take him back, volunteering to stay there with him. Reality is safe once again.
name: What I Did For Love!
The Price Is Murder!
Into The Jaws Of Death!

description:
Notes

  • Features the Hostess Twinkies ad, Spider-Man And The "Twinkie Takers"
  • The second story, Skull-Face is incorrectly credited as appearing in Mystic #6, however, it originally appeared in Mystery Tales #6.
name: ...And Fear Shall Follow!

description: When the Thundercats homeworld is destroyed, a small group of survivors crash-land on the mysterious green world known as Third Earth. They soon find themselves in a desperate fight for survival against their mortal enemies the Mutants. However, things go from bad to worse when their battle with the vile Mutants awakens Mumm-Ra, an ancient ogre-mage whose dark magic powers know no rival.
name: Survival Run

description: Lion-O, leader of the Thundercats and armed with the mystical Sword of Omens, defends his people and the benevolent denizens of third Earth against Mumm-Ra and the other malevolent creatures that hide in the shadows and cracks of this strange new world.
name: Tears Of Sunrise

description: Panthro steps to the forefront to help Tessa, a beautiful young witch, fulfill her destiny.
name: Panthro Stands Alone!

description: One-by-one the Thundercats fall. Can even Lion-O stand alone against the power of Mumm-Ra, the Ever-Living?! Plus, who is the mysterious Lynxana the Hunter?
name: Jaga Quest! (Wanted)

description: The Thundercats are at the mercy of the sinister Mutants. Can Lion-O and his new "partner," Lynxana the Hunter, free them from Castle Plun-Darr before its too late?
name: Things Look Bad For Lion-O - - Then Again Things Are Tough All Over!

description: Lion-O and Cheetara face the most difficult decision of their lives. They are presented with a chance to return to their homeworld of Thundera, but at what cost?
name: Back To Thundera!

description: The Thundercats Olympics are interrupted when the diabolical Mutants attack in full force.
name: "To The Victor, The Spoils"

description: When an ancient curse befalls the Thundercats it is up to the super strong Panthro to save the day.
name: Graveyard of Memories

description: When something threatens to shake the Cats Lair down to its very foundation, the Thundercats head below to investigate and come face-to-face with the mysterious Molemen.
When a nearby village comes under the attack of the Berserkers it fall to the Thundercats to stop these pirates.
The Thundercats are defeated. Now the only who can save the day is... Snarf?!
Can even the brave Thundercats prevail when the greatest big game hunter in the galaxy arrives on Third Earth looking for sport?
In order to find the mysterious Time Capsule the Thundercats must brave the dangers of the wilds of Third Earth.
Can Lion-O and Snarf hope to survive when they fall into the trap of Mumm-Ra, the Ever-Living?
When Wilykit and Wilykat rescue a local villager from a horde of gargoyles they soon find themselves on a quest to discover the mysteries and dangers that lie within the foreboding Black Tower.

When the Ro-Bears come under attack the Thundercats soon find themselves face-to-face with Mumm-Ra, the Ever-Living. Plus, who is Ta-She and, what is her mysterious connection to the Thundercats greatest enemy?
Its the dual of the century when Lion-O and the Sword of Omens face off against a mysterious Black Knight and the legendary Excalibur!

When a baby is left on the doorstep Snarf becomes a father. However, the Mutants kidnap the critter. But these villains will soon discover that its easier to deal with the Thundercats than it is rearing a new born. A humorous tale in the life of the Thundercats.
name: Father Snarf

description: As the Thundercats battle Mumm-Ra in the form of a fire-breathing dragon, Vultureman unleashes his latest invention -evil robot versions of the Thunderkittens.
Lion-O faces a deadly new adversary and a monstrous new terror five fathoms below the sea.
The Thundercats are challenged like never before when Mumm-Ra unleashes their evil twins!
name: Through a Dark Glass!!

description: When Optimus Prime's ship full of Autobots is attacked by Megatron and the Decepticons, the spaceship crash-lands on Earth. Several million years later, the robots wake up and continue their fight on this strange new world.
name: The Transformers

description: As the war between the Autobots and Decepticons rages on, an Autobot named Bumblebee makes friends with teenager Buster Witwicky, unwittingly drawing him and his father into the conflict.
name: Power Play!

description:
As the Transfomers' battle escalates, Peter Parker jumps into the fray to save the day as Spider-Man. The trouble is, he doesn't understand the difference between the heroes and the villains.

NOTE #1: Spider-Man appears here in his alien black suit symbiote, as seen in Secret Wars. Although Peter is completely in control in this story, this is the same alien symbiote that will eventually become Venom.

NOTE #2: Spider-Man (in his traditional red outfit) would face off against Megatron again in New Avengers/Transformers. While Peter was from the same Marvel continuity, the Transformers were from a different continuity in IDW, so no mention is made between them of their previous meeting.

NOTE #3: Mike Zeck didn't draw this cover
name: Prisoner Of War!

description:
The Decepticons have been provided with a suitable fuel by the human Sparky Witnicky.

As the Decepticons make their preparations for a final attack on the Autobots, the Autobots argue amongst themselves as to the actions of Sparky and the role of humans in general. During the argument, Sparky suffers a heart attack and is taken to the local hospital by the Autobot Ratchet.

Finally, the Decepticons attack leading to a massive battle. When the Decepticons have essentially beaten the Autobots, the Decepticons all collapse due to a hidden acid Sparky put in the fuel he created for them. However, as the Autobots, fatigued from the battle, celebrate the apparent victory over the Decepticons, the Decepticon Shockwave appears to finish off the weakened Autobots.
name: The Last Stand

description:
In issue #4, a human named Sparkplug Witwicky poisoned fuel used by both Autobots and Decepticons which caused both sides to fall in battle. At the conclusion of the battle, Shockwave arrived to finish off the Autobots.

Following Shockwave's destruction, Shockwave began to rebuild the decepticons while relegating Megatron to second in command.

Megatron, never one to accept being second in command, pretended to accept his new position while plotting to retake command of the Decepticons from Shockwave.

Unknown to Shockwave, the Autobot Ratchet survived the assault. Ratchet returns to the Ark to find that it is now controlled by the Decepticons. Ratchet, with the help of a human named Buster Witwicky, returns to the Ark. Inside the Ark, Buster finds the remains of the Autobots, including the severed head of Optimus Prime.
name: The New Order
The Next Best Thing To Being There

description: The Autobots battle the Decepticons at a Rock and Roll concert.
name: Rock And Roll-Out!

description: The government wants to get Transformer hysteria under control, so they create a scapegoat - in the form of "Robot-Master," as played by a washed-up comic book artist. And as it turns out, Megatron actually sees an advantage in letting humans keep their misconceptions.
name: I, Robot Master!

description: A dark two-part story that moves away from Earth to let the readers know what's been happening on the Transformers' home planet of Cybertron, as Blaster and the other Autobots try to fight the Deceptions' tyrannical rule there.
name: Return To Cybertron Part 1: The Smelting Pool!

description: In the conclusion of the two-part arc, Blaster must prevent the Deceptions from escaping through a space bridge from Cybertron to Earth.
name: Return To Cybertron Part 2: The Bridge To Nowhere

description: The Autobots attack the Decepticons in order to discover the secret transformation matrix of Devastator. Meanwhile, Megatron plans a secret attack on Autobot base where he and his troops run into the newly built Omega Supreme. Starscream, Skywarp, Thundercracker, Frenzy, Rumble and Buzzsaw all die while fighting the enormous Autobot.
name: Command Performances

description: The Aerialbots battle the new seekers
name: Aerialbots Over America

description: While Skids and Donny Finkleberg attempt to locate the Cybertronian Autobots, Megatron sends the Stunticons to intercept.
name: Heavy Traffic

description: Megatron orders Runabout and Runamuck to send a message to Optimus Prime.
name: Decepticon Graffiti

description:
In this pivotal issue, Optimus Prime and Megatron finally face off in a fight to the death in a virtual world, with the winner being the only one left standing in the real world.

This issue takes place after G.I. Joe/Transformers issue #1 and before issue #2.
name: Afterdeath

description: Shockwave sends the Predakons from Cybertron to assassinate Magatron.
name: Gone but not Forgotten

description: Ratchet feels blue as he couldn't save Optimus Prime and the ark is invaded by the Mechanic
name: Funeral for a Friend

description: Blaster gets infected by the scraplets while fighting the decepticon triple changers
name: Crater Critters

description: Ratbat uses a special set of flashing lights at the end of the "Wash and Roll" car wash to hypnotize human beings into doing the Decepticons' bidding. Buster discovers the plan when Jesse gets hypnotized.
name: Buster Witwicky and the Car Wash Of Doom

description: Reprints Marvel UK's The Transformers #9-10
name: Man of Iron - Part 1

description: Reprints Marvel UK's The Transformers #11-12
name: Man of Iron - Part 2

description:
Assault of the Savage Seacons!

The Autobots become suspicious (rightly so) when the Decepticons begin promoting their desert island base as a resort called "Club Con." They suspect that the Decepticons are using their guests as human shields so that they can operate without Autobot intervention. Blaster and Jesse go undercover to investigate in hopes of uncovering the latest Decepticon scheme as well as the whereabouts of the missing Buster. In the process, they encounter the Seacons...
name: The Underbase Saga (Pt 1): Club Con!

description: The return of Megatron... and the end of Optimus Prime?!?
name: The Underbase Saga (Pt 2): The Flames of Boltax!
